result.execSummary:
The defendant Tiffani A. Milbradt was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).
  • Disorderly Conduct (Wood Co. Case #15CM420), a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: 2:32pm Attorney David Deda appeared.  Mark T. Fuhr appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Atty. Deda requests judgment be amended as to count 1 - 48 days jail, instead of 50 days.  DA has no objection.  Court so orders.

2:37 pm - DA calls case and states appearances.  Defendant Tiffani A. Milbradt in court with attorney David Deda.  Defendant in custody.  Mark T. Fuhr appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Parties have received and acknowledge receipt of revocation packet.  DA can certify victims rights compliance.  Comments and request by Deda.  Court comments, and imposes:  50 days jail on Ct 1, 45 days on count 2, cs to each other.  Reimpose all prior monetary amounts. 30 days to pay upon release from jail.   Jail credit of 55 days.
Sentencing hearing on revocation on August 18, 2016 at 02:30 pm.
Application for consolidation, consents for consolidation and order approving consolidation

10:04 am - Defendant Tiffani A. Milbradt appeared with attorney David Deda.  Mark T. Fuhr appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  DA states agreement regarding this case and consolidated Wood Co. case.  Defendant makes statement. Exam by Court. DA files amended complaint to include Wood Co. charge.   Complaint acknowledged, reading waived. DE pleads NO CONTEST to both counts.   Court questions DE regarding the plea and plea questionnaire.  DA explains elements of charge.  Court finds plea/waiver to be free, etc.  Court finds factual basis does exist.  DA certifies victims rights compliance. Court accepts plea, finds DE guilty and orders entry of JOC on both counts and on motion of DA dismisses 15TR171 & 15TR172. Comments by parties.  Comments and ruling by Court. Appeal rights given.
